# Keep the ACR build-context upload small AND keep secrets out of it.
#
# The WebApiDemo Dockerfile only COPYs:
#   - root: Directory.Build.props, Directory.Build.targets, global.json
#   - src/PostQuantum.Hybrid, src/PostQuantum.Hybrid.Envelopes,
#     src/PostQuantum.Hybrid.AspNetCore, src/PostQuantum.Hybrid.Analyzers
#   - samples/Directory.Build.props, samples/WebApiDemo/
# Everything else is dead weight — and a few things are actively dangerous
# (secret API keys at the repo root that are .gitignored but would still
# ship in the build-context tar if not excluded here).
#
# Update this file when the Dockerfile starts COPYing something new.

# --- SECRETS — must never ship in the build context ---
# These also appear in .gitignore, but .dockerignore is independent — both
# rules must be in place to keep keys out of ACR's build-context storage.
# Patterns are deliberately recursive (**/) so a key file in any subfolder
# is caught too, not just at the repo root.
**/*.key
**/*.key.txt
**/Nuget*.key*
**/nuget.key*
**/Marketplace*.key*
**/*.pfx
**/*.snk
**/*.pem
**/secrets.json

# --- Build outputs and test artifacts ---
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/TestResults/
**/StrykerOutput*/
**/CoverageReport/
**/coverage*.xml
**/*.binlog
artifacts/

# --- Repo machinery the Dockerfile does not need ---
.git/
.github/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.editorconfig
.well-known/
.vs/
.vscode/
.idea/

# --- Top-level directories the Dockerfile does not COPY ---
benchmarks/
docs/
docs-site/
fuzz/
scripts/
templates/
tests/
tools/
vscode-extension/

# --- Other samples (Dockerfile only COPYs samples/Directory.Build.props
#     and samples/WebApiDemo/) ---
samples/BasicDemo/
samples/EnvelopesDemo/
samples/KemEncryption/
samples/KeyPersistence/
samples/KeyRotationDemo/
samples/LargeFileEncryption/
samples/SecureMessenger/
samples/SignedDocument/
samples/README.md

# --- Misc files at the repo root the Dockerfile does not need ---
# (Per-project READMEs under src/ are still copied via src/<project>/ to
# keep PackageReadmeFile happy if anything below publish ever tries to
# resolve them; the repo-root markdown files are dead weight here.)
CHANGELOG.md
CLAUDE.md
CONTRIBUTING.md
HARDENING-CHECKLIST.md
KNOWN-GAPS.md
README.md
SECURITY.md
LICENSE
gem4.md
PostQuantum.Hybrid.slnx
stryker-config.json
